1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,530
One.

2
00:00:00,880 --> 00:00:03,890
Expect future obstacles and difficulties.

3
00:00:04,160 --> 00:00:08,530
Every venture presents risks, problems, and uncertainties.

4
00:00:09,040 --> 00:00:13,570
Let's suppose you wanted to drive your car from Chicago to Los Angeles,

5
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:19,330
but you insisted on waiting until you had absolute assurance that there would be no detours,

6
00:00:19,440 --> 00:00:24,690
no motor trouble, no bad weather, no drunken drivers, no risk of any kind.

7
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:26,210
When would you start?

8
00:00:26,480 --> 00:00:27,089
Never.

9
00:00:27,440 --> 00:00:31,729
In planning your trip to Los Angeles, it makes sense to map your route,

10
00:00:31,760 --> 00:00:37,650
check your car, in other ways to eliminate as much risk as possible before you start.

11
00:00:37,920 --> 00:00:40,770
But you can't eliminate all risks.

12
00:00:40,770 --> 00:00:43,089
2.

13
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:46,849
Meet problems and obstacles as they arise.

14
00:00:47,120 --> 00:00:53,729
The test of a successful person is not the ability to eliminate all problems before he takes action,

15
00:00:53,840 --> 00:00:59,089
but rather the ability to find solutions to difficulties when he encounters them.

16
00:00:59,440 --> 00:01:05,249
In business, marriage, or in any activity, cross bridges when you come to them.

17
00:01:07,440 --> 00:01:11,410
We can't buy an insurance policy against all problems.

18
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:15,170
Make up your mind to do something about your ideas.
